Title: Object: Pompey's pillar
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 14 in volume I: a large column standing in a field in the centre, three men turning back to two women by a tent in the left foreground, two men riding horses accompanied by their men on the right; after Mayer; published state. 1802 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.I.14)
